<div class="panel" id="screenshots">
  <div class="container">

    <header class="page-header">
      <h3>Looking for work sucks rocks.</h3>
      <h1>Suitor makes it suck less.</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="image">
        <%= image_tag("screenshots/post-listing-screen.png", :alt => "Post lisings") %>
      </div>

      <div class="text">
        <p>If you've looked for a job at any point during the last ten years, you're probably well aware that things are rather&hellip; shall we say, <em>dismal</em>. Apparently the economy is in kind of rough shape. Who know?</p>
        <p>So you end up sending out <em>hundreds</em> of resumes. (Unless you're more hire-able than we are, in which case, you probably want to <a href="http://forbes.com">go elsewhere now</a>.)</p>
        <p><strong>How do you keep track of it all?</strong></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="text">
      <p>Suitor was built to help you keep track of the jobs you're interested in. Want to <strong>track deadlines &amp; interviews</strong>? <em>Done.</em> Need <strong>reminders to follow-up</strong> on an application? <em>You got 'em.</em> Just want to <strong>remember</strong> what you sent, who you sent it to, and when you sent it? <em>Okay.</em> How about <strong>visual indicators of your progress?</strong> Sure thing!
      </div>

      <div class="image">
        <%= image_tag("screenshots/add-job-post.png", :alt => "Add a job posting") %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="image">
        <%= image_tag("screenshots/schedule-interview.png", :alt => "Schedule an interview") %>
      </div>

      <div class="text">
        <p>We've got a lot more planned for Suitor&mdash;like social media and iCal integration, automatic email submissions, integration with existing job posting sites&mdash;down the line. The project is <a href="http://github.com/sarahsemark/suitor">open-source</a>, so contributions and bug reports are always welcome, and you can help us make it better. </p>
        <p><a class="jump" href="#signup">Want to <strong>give it a try</strong>?</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>


  </div>
  <a class="next jump" href="#signup"><i class="icon-arrow-down9"><span>Next panel</span></i></a>
</div>




